  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Anne Morton thanks Maria Weston Chapman for a copy of the Liberty Bell. She wants Maria to write an encouraging letter to her society. She asks if a &quot;sew&apos;d Carpet&quot; would sell at the anti-slavery fair. Morton says: &quot;There are many right hearted men and women in the Free Church of Scotland, who will be found fighting in the Anti-Slavery cause.&quot; Morton praises James N. Buffum and Frederick Douglass. She gives the dates of the meetings of her society.</subfield>
